    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="210"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1891</hi>.</date> (Received December
                        3.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 214.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to refer to my No. 202, of 16th September,
                    and to say that the elections held on 18th of present month resulted very nearly
                    as I then predicted.</p>
                <p>In the new Senate there will be but 3 Conservatives or members of the Clerical
                    party, the other 29 being composed of the different groups of Liberals and
                    Radicals; and in the Chamber of Deputies, 35 Conservatives and 59 Liberals and
                    Radicals. There is also a substantial majority <pb facs="0309" n="203"
                        xml:id="pg_203"/> of the presidential electors on the side of the Liberal
                    party, but up to the present there is no certainty, and even very little idea,
                    as to who will be selected for the Presidency.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Patrick Egan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
